args: (Wait. This preternatural sensation...\nAh! These people must beâ€”!)
Something wrong, child? You have\nthe gravest look on your face.
I'm just a bit lightheaded.\nCan you tell me when the festival begins?
After sundown, of course. You can't\nenjoy the lanterns till after dark, love.
Sure, the festival's famous for 'em!\nIsn't that what you've come to see?
Ah, yes, of course. It would seem the long\ntrip here has taken a toll on my memory.
Oh, you poor thing. You're welcome to\nrest a spell at my home, if you like.
That is terribly kind of you, ma'am, but\nI think I'll putter around the village a\nbit before the festival begins.
(The dead ordinarily return to mana\nand flow across the world. But this...)
(In rare cases, the soul cannot come to\nterms with death and instead lingers in\nthe place where its body passed on.)
You forgot the dinner I packed you,\nsweetheart. Good luck with the festival\nsetup.
You liar! You promised we'd always,\nALWAYS watch the lanterns together!
Again, I already said I was sorry.\nI just can't make it this year, okay?
(The ebb and flow of daily lifeâ€”\nthe same as you'd see in any town.\nBut everyone here is...)
(It is said that the dead resent the living.\nIf these people learn that I'm aliveâ€”)
Y-you there. You're not one of the villagers.\nAre you, er...real?
I'm guessing you wandered in here too?

Oh, thank heavens! I was resting in this
abandoned house I found, and when I
awoke, I was here, among all these
people. Then that THING attacked me!
P-please, you've gotta help me.\nI just want to go home! Please!
Sorry, dearie, but I don't think that's\ngoing to happen. You're alreadyâ€”
Now, now. What's all the commotion here?
Y-you! Get me out of here! I beg you!
Poor soul. I think the heat's gotten to him.\nCome, love. Rest awhile.
I'll take him to my house. It's right\non the river, so it stays nice and cool.
Aww, don't be shy. If you're too tired to\nwalk, we'll carry you there.
Stop! N-no, let go! LET ME GOOO!
The heat always drives folks a little batty.\nSure you don't need to come rest as well?
As I thought. Some sort of barrier is\nblocking my means of egress.
It's safe to assume this place is a\nmanifestation of these people's collective\nmemory, fueled by their regret at passing.
If what I've read is true,\nthere's only one way out.
I must ease their regret and guide them\nback to the source of mana where they\nbelong. First, to discern the cause...
...Whoever is watching, I can feel your\neyes on me.
Hm. They're gone. Hopefully that\ndoesn't mean they've realized I'm alive.
Is that a weary festival-goer I spy?
Hello, ma'am. I grew tired from my stroll,\nso I'm just resting in the shade a bit.
Really, now. You should follow me, then.\nI have just the thing.
(Was she the one watching me?\nThose weren't the footsteps of an\nelderly woman.)
Are you listening, dear? Don't tell me\nthe heat's sapped your hearing, too.
(For now, I need to avoid arousing\nany suspicion.)
There. A nice, frosty flagon of grape juice.\nWe make it every year. There's plenty,\nso just holler if you'd like more.
This drink's a festival tradition, you know.
I really shouldn't, but thank you.
It's the village's pride and joy.\nSurely a little taste wouldn't hurt.
(I can't let this past my lips...)
Come, come. Bottoms up, love.\nOr is there some reason you don't want to?
(I've read the legends. Sup upon the\nofferings of the dead, and you'll be unable\nto return to the realm of the living.)
You're a strange one, even for a stranger.\nCould you beâ€”
Oh no! I got juice all over your pretty\nclothes! I'm so sorry!
Worry not. I just need to wash it before it\ndries. Can you point me to some water?
The village well is just over there.
That will do nicely, thank you.
But I can't let my guard down. I need to\nfind what's become of Douleur, too.
Um... I'm really sorry about before, ma'am.
Oh, it's you. Don't worry, dearie.\nI'm not upset in the slightest.
But you were planning to show that\nyukata to your boyfriend, weren't you?
My boyfriend? Now what would make you\nthink that?
The way you're all done up, of course!\nI'm a romantic too, so I've got a sense\nfor this sort of thing.
Heh heh... Sorry to disappoint you,\nbut this raven is flying solo today.
Well, that's a shame.\nOh, that's right! I wanted to offer\nyou my handkerchief to clean up.
Folded crisp and even... She must have\nbeen quite the fastidious little girl in life.
Mm? Something fell out when\nI unfolded it. A...torn scrap?
This village is trapped\nin a tragedy 40 years past.\nPlease help us.
A message? What's more, this paper...
The page is infused with mana.\nThis was a piece of Douleur!
